##  Overview
This lab simulates common IT support networking issues and demonstrates how they are diagnosed and resolved using basic troubleshooting tools.

---

##  Tools Used
- Windows 10/11 VM
- Command Prompt
- Network utilities (ipconfig, ping, nslookup, tracert)

---

##  Scenarios Practiced

### 1. No Internet Connection
- Checked IP configuration using `ipconfig`
- Verified gateway settings
- Restarted network adapter
- Fixed incorrect IP assignment

---

### 2. DNS Issues
- User could not access websites by name
- Used `nslookup` to test DNS resolution
- Flushed DNS cache using `ipconfig /flushdns`
- Resolved by correcting DNS server settings

---

### 3. Connectivity Testing
- Used `ping` to test local and external connectivity
- Used `tracert` to trace network path issues

---

##  Skills Practiced
- Network troubleshooting
- DNS resolution
- IP configuration analysis
- Basic diagnostic commands

---

##  What I Learned
This lab helped me understand how to identify and resolve common network issues that are frequently encountered in IT support roles.
